    "title": "Statistics II",
    "section": "",
    "text": "Preface\nThis course introduces postgraduate students to advanced statistical methods used in the quantitative social, educational, and behavioral sciences. Students will learn:\n\nData management in R.\nAnalysis of Variance (ANOVA) Designs.\nMultiple Linear Regression. Interaction between variables.\nMediation and Path Analysis.\nFactor Analysis.\nPrinciples of Evidence Synthesis (Systematic reviews and Meta-analysis).",
