  {
    "objectID": "intro.html#matrix-2-dimensional-atomic-vector",
    "href": "intro.html#matrix-2-dimensional-atomic-vector",
    "title": "1  Basic data structures in R",
    "section": "1.2 Matrix (2-dimensional atomic vector)",
    "text": "1.2 Matrix (2-dimensional atomic vector)\n\na &lt;- c(2, 1, 4, 5, 3, 7) # numeric vector with six elements\n\n\n# Matrices are constructed column-wise starting in the “upper left” corner \n# and running down the columns\nA &lt;- matrix(a, nrow=2, ncol=3)\nA\n\n     [,1] [,2] [,3]\n[1,]    2    4    3\n[2,]    1    5    7",
    "crumbs": [
      "<span class='chapter-number'>1</span>  <span class='chapter-title'>Basic data structures in R</span>"
    ]
