  {
    "objectID": "intro.html#data-frame-generic-vector-or-list",
    "href": "intro.html#data-frame-generic-vector-or-list",
    "title": "1  Basic data structures in R",
    "section": "1.3 Data frame (generic vector or list)",
    "text": "1.3 Data frame (generic vector or list)\n\n# build data frames using vectors\n\npatientID &lt;- c(1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8)\n\nage &lt;- c(25, 30, 28, 22, 31, 45, 37, 43)\n\nweight &lt;- c(94, 83, 71, 87, 94, 73, 89, 74)\n\ndiabetes &lt;- c(\"Type 1\", \"Type 2\", \"Type 1\", \"Type 1\",\n              \"Type 2\", \"Type 1\", \"Type 1\", \"Type 2\")\n\n\n\n# create the dataframe\ndat &lt;- data.frame(patientID, age, weight, diabetes) # insert all the variables\ndat\n\n  patientID age weight diabetes\n1         1  25     94   Type 1\n2         2  30     83   Type 2\n3         3  28     71   Type 1\n4         4  22     87   Type 1\n5         5  31     94   Type 2\n6         6  45     73   Type 1\n7         7  37     89   Type 1\n8         8  43     74   Type 2\n\n\n\ntypeof(dat)\n\n[1] \"list\"\n\nclass(dat)\n\n[1] \"data.frame\"",
    "crumbs": [
      "<span class='chapter-number'>1</span>  <span class='chapter-title'>Basic data structures in R</span>"
    ]
